   @phlix/ui — Color tokens (Nocturne design system, R0.1)

   Semantic, [data-theme]-scoped token set. :root defaults to Nocturne so the
   tokens resolve even when no data-theme attribute is set (back-compat).
   The useTheme() composable (R1) sets [data-theme] on <html>.

   Legacy --color-* names are kept as ALIASES pointing at the new tokens, and
   are re-declared inside EACH theme block so per-subtree theming (e.g. an R4
   appearance-preview swatch) resolves correctly — CSS var() substitution uses
   the referenced property's value on the same element.

   Atmosphere hooks (--grain-opacity / --vignette / --ambient) live here too.
   Elevation lives in shadow.css; motion in motion.css; density in density.css.
   ============================================================================ */

/* ---- Accent ramp — projector amber. Theme-invariant (amber identity is constant). ---- */
:root {
  --amber-50:  #fff8ec;
  --amber-100: #ffedcc;
  --amber-200: #ffd894;
  --amber-300: #ffbf5c;
  --amber-400: #fbab36;
  --amber-500: #f5a524;   /* primary accent */
  --amber-600: #d98209;
  --amber-700: #b4610a;
  --amber-800: #924d10;
  --amber-900: #783f11;
  --amber-950: #441f06;
  --accent-contrast: #2a1804;   /* ink on amber fills */
}

/* =============================  THEME: Nocturne (dark, default)  =========== */
:root,
[data-theme='nocturne'] {
  color-scheme: dark;

  --accent:        var(--amber-500);
  --accent-hover:  var(--amber-400);
  --accent-active: var(--amber-600);
  --accent-soft:   rgba(245, 165, 36, 0.14);
  --accent-ring:   rgba(245, 165, 36, 0.55);
  --accent-text:   var(--amber-500);   /* amber AS foreground text/icon — AA (≥4.5:1) on bg/surface */

  --bg:            #0b0a08;
  --surface:       #16130f;
  --surface-2:     #2

